headlines.description: — Ja Morant had 23 points and eight assists playing in front of relatives and friends, Desmond Bane added 19 points and 10 rebounds and the Memphis Grizzlies beat the Charlotte Hornets 131-107 on Wednesday night for their fourth straight win.
headlines.shortLinkText: Morant, Grizzlies overpower Hornets for 4th straight win

headlines.description: — Evan Mobley couldn't remember the last time he made a winning shot. He'll never forget his first one in the NBA.
headlines.shortLinkText: Evan Mobley hits late jumper, Cavaliers beat Suns 90-88

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at Orlando Magic

headlines.description: — Paolo Banchero had 25 points, eight rebounds and seven assists, and the Orlando Magic beat the Oklahoma City Thunder 126-115 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Paolo Banchero, Magic turn back Thunder 126-115

headlines.description: — De’Anthony Melton hit a go-ahead 3-pointer late in overtime and James Harden scored 26 points to help a Philadelphia 76ers team playing without Joel Embiid beat the Indiana Pacers 129-126 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Without Embiid, 76ers push past Pacers 129-126 in OT

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — Asked before the game about his team's victory over the Knicks last week, Spurs coach Gregg Popovich was quick to note that Jalen Brunson didn't play.
headlines.shortLinkText: Brunson scores career-best 38, Knicks edge Spurs 117-114

headlines.description: — Giannis Antetokounmpo had 30 points, 10 assists and a season-high 21 rebounds for his second triple-double of the season, Grayson Allen hit a tiebreaking 3-pointer with 11.6 seconds to go in overtime and the Milwaukee Bucks beat the Toronto Raptors...
headlines.shortLinkText: Antetokounmpo has season-high 21 rebounds, Bucks top Raptors

headlines.description: — DeMar DeRozan and Patrick Williams each scored 22 points, and the Chicago Bulls stopped Brooklyn's 12-game win streak with a 121-112 victory over Kevin Durant and the Nets on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Durant scores 44, but Bulls snap Nets' 12-game win streak

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at Minnesota Timberwolves

headlines.description: — Anthony Edwards scored 13 of his 32 points in the fourth quarter, Rudy Gobert had 17 points and 12 rebounds, and the Minnesota Timberwolves beat the Portland Trail Blazers 113-106 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Edwards scores 32, helps Wolves close out Blazers 113-106

events.name: Houston Rockets at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — CJ McCollum scored 28 points and the short-handed Pelicans opened up a 31-point lead en route to a 119-108 victory over the struggling Houston Rockets on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: McCollum leads short-handed Pelicans past Rockets, 119-108

events.name: Detroit Pistons at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — The final play had been drawn for Bojan Bogdanovic, then Saddiq Bey suddenly found the ball in his hands with no time to think, so he just let it fly.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bey beats buzzer with 3, Pistons beat Warriors 122-119

events.name: Miami Heat at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — Dennis Schröder scored 14 of his season-high 32 points in the fourth quarter and the undermanned Los Angeles Lakers improbably overcame LeBron James’ absence for a 112-109 victory over the Miami Heat on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Schröder propels Lakers past Heat 112-109 without LeBron, AD

headlines.description: — De’Andre Hunter and John Collins each scored 22 points and the Atlanta Hawks beat the Sacramento Kings 120-117 on Wednesday night to end a four-game slide.
headlines.shortLinkText: Hunter, Collins star as Hawks beat Kings 120-117
